quiPeutBeneficier.body:
Full unemployment is open to the worker whose employment contract has ended (dismissal, resignation, end of fixed-term contract, mutual termination…) and who meets several basic conditions:

- having worked a sufficient number of days during the reference period preceding the claim (the threshold increases with age);
- being registered as a job seeker with the regional service (FOREM in Wallonia, ACTIRIS in Brussels, VDAB in Flanders, ADG in the German-speaking Community);
- being available for the labour market (fit, willing to accept suitable employment, to follow training, etc.);
- not already being covered by another replacement income (insurance fund, pension, full-time pay…).

Self-employed people who voluntarily contributed to the employee unemployment scheme and young people on first registration (vocational integration period) follow specific rules.

Public reference: www.onem.be.
